I know Rodriguez in an interview saying this is not white-washing because the author "Yukito Kishiro" didn't write for this to set in an Asian world.  I have a problem with that comment right there.  What is an "Asian World"?  With character names such as Daisuke Ido and Chiren, really?  Imagine Captain America being Chinese? or Black Panther being white?  I understand that a film needs to make money and Asian stars are not as bankable right now, but my problem is, you look at the cast list of this movie and there are 2 Asian actors playing sidekicks.  2 Asian actors out of a cast of many in a Japanese Manga film?  I am not usually this controversial (I mean, I run DIY channel for godsakes) but just needed to speak out about this.
